Wrkpod, Inc. - NOC Escalation – Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)
Network & Performance Data Collection
Purpose
To ensure complete and standardized data is gathered before escalating any network-related issues (e.g., slow internet, high latency, unstable connection) to the NOC team.
 All screenshots and test results must be attached to the escalation ticket or email.

1. Prepare the Workstation
Before running any tests, ensure accurate network readings:
Disable VPN


Disconnect or turn off any active VPN connections.


Use LAN Only


Turn off Wi-Fi.


Ensure the device is connected via LAN (Ethernet) cable only.



2. Collect Network Configuration Details
Internal & Full IP Details
Open Command Prompt or PowerShell


Run the command:

 ipconfig /all


Screenshot the full output


External/Public IP
Go to:https://ifconfig.com/
Screenshot the page showing the public IP




3. Run Performance & Latency Tests
Perform all 3 tests below and take screenshots.
a. Speedtest.net
Go to: https://www.speedtest.net


Set server to: Makati – Rise


Run test and screenshot Ping, Download, Upload


b. M-Lab Test
Use Google’s internet speed test or: https://speed.measurementlab.net


Run Network Diagnostic Test and screenshot results


c. Bufferbloat (Waveform) Test
Search: “bufferbloat test” or open https://www.waveform.com/tools/bufferbloat from any browser
Run test fully and screenshot the final results (showing latency rating)



4. Capture Workstation Performance
Open Task Manager (Ctrl+Shift+Esc)


Go to Performance tab


Screenshot CPU, Memory, and Network usage graphs



5. Tracert the target IP
Open Command Prompt


Type and enter: Tracert [Target IP Address]


Screenshot the result
6. Prepare for Escalation
Before submitting to NOC/JD:
✅ Attach all screenshots collected from:
Section 2: Network Configuration


Section 3: Speed & Latency Tests


Section 4: System Performance
Section 5: Tracert the target IP


✅ Use a clear subject line:
Example: Network Performance Issue – [Workstation Name / IP]

End of Procedure
